  "texts": [
    "In this setting, the data analyst is tasked with privately releasing the answers to a set of statistical queries computed with respect to a (sensitive) data set.",
    "This general problem captures a number of important use cases.",
    "For instance, releasing private summary data for the 2020 US Census (Abowd et al., 2022) can be seen as an instance of private query release.",
    "Some works study the effect of public data in these settings (Bassily, Cheu, et al., 2020; Ji & Elkan, 2013; T. Liu et al., 2021; M. Wang et al., 2017), both theoretically and empirically.",
    "A recent challenge organized by NIST (National Institute of Standards and Technology) focuses on temporal map data (NIST, 2020), and provides participants with public data from a different year to help make predictions."
  ],
